Hello Chief Delphi community!
We are having problems regulating the swerve wheels, we offset with the raw absolute encoder values, we update the values, but it continues to deregulate.
So when we offset again the values change completely, an example is our back left wheel, which the values of the raw absolute encoder changes between 58 and 352, switching between these two values.
We use the YAGSL and the absolute encoder MA3.

Last season we had exactly this problem and students couldn’t figure out what was wrong. It was on the pivot with a different encoder (CANcoder). We were using a Falcon 500/TalonFX and a gearbox. We had to use the encoder in the motor to circumvent the problem. I tried to troubleshoot but what failed every time for the students never failed for me with a similar test bed so there was no resolution. I know we tried different encoders and I’m not sure if we tried different motors. CTRE suggested it is usually robot software error that causes any bizarre behavior but we had no other statements in our code that manipulated those devices.
